<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFE3FFC2A5CDFC021BADFB30" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFE3FFC2A5CDFC021FD1FC35" blockId="19.[136,494,986,1013]" box="[136,494,986,1013]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<heading id="D0A781CFFFE3FFC2A5CDFC021FD1FC35" box="[136,494,986,1013]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" reason="4">
7. 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFE3FFC2A5E1FC031FD5FC35" authority="Linnaeus (1753: 633)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityPageNumber="633" authorityYear="1753" box="[164,490,986,1013]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Lippia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE3FFC2A5E1FC031ED0FC34" bold="true" box="[164,239,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Lippia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE3FFC2A5B3FC031FD5FC35" author="Linnaeus, C. von" box="[246,490,986,1013]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 1200" refId="ref35181" refString="Linnaeus, C. von (1753) Species Plantarum. L. Salvius, Stockholm, pp. 1 - 1200." type="book chapter" year="1753">Linnaeus (1753: 633)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFE3FFC2A5CDFBFB1BADFB30" blockId="19.[136,1452,1058,1516]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Shrubs or subshrubs, monoecious, branches without prickles, aromatic. Leaves petiolate, glands near to the petiole absent. Inflorescences axillary, simple, racemes capituliform, compact, multiflorous, rachis elongated or not in fructification;; bracts chartaceous, green, bracteoles absent. Flowers sessile; calyx tubular, shorter than the corolla, membranaceous, green, 2-lobed, accrescent in fruit; corolla zygomorphic, 5-lobed, 2-labiate; stamens 4, included, didynamous, superior pair without connective appendages, thecae parallel; ovary 1-carpelate, 2-loculate, ovules 1 per locule, stigma oblique. Fruit a schizocarp, with 2 cluses or a drupe with 2 pyrenes, brown, external surface smooth.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFE3FFC2A5F8FB221EF0FA2C" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFE3FFC2A5F8FB221EF0FA2C" blockId="19.[136,1452,1058,1516]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFE3FFC2A5F8FB221F39FAD4" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[189,262,1275,1300]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Lippia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE3FFC2A5F8FB221F39FAD4" box="[189,262,1275,1300]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Lippia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is part of the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFE3FFC2A493FB221D25FAD4" authority="(Marx et al. 2010)" baseAuthorityName="Marx" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[470,794,1274,1301]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Lantaneae">
Lantaneae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE3FFC2A712FB231D2DFAD4" author="Marx, H. &amp; O'Leary, N. &amp; Yuan, Y. &amp; Lu-Irving, P. &amp; Tank, D. &amp; Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R." box="[599,786,1274,1300]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1647 - 1663" refId="ref35509" refString="Marx, H., O'Leary, N., Yuan, Y., Lu-Irving, P., Tank, D., Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R. (2010) A molecular phylogeny and classification of Verbenaceae. American Journal of Botany 97: 1647 - 1663. https: // doi. org / 10.3732 / ajb. 1000144" type="journal article" year="2010">
Marx 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE3FFC2A7DEFB221CEDFAD4" box="[667,722,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and has 140 species distributed throughout the tropical and subtropical America, with a few representatives in the east of Africa (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE3FFC2A6C8FAC71A73FAF8" author="Marx, H. &amp; O'Leary, N. &amp; Yuan, Y. &amp; Lu-Irving, P. &amp; Tank, D. &amp; Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R." box="[909,1100,1310,1336]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1647 - 1663" refId="ref35509" refString="Marx, H., O'Leary, N., Yuan, Y., Lu-Irving, P., Tank, D., Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R. (2010) A molecular phylogeny and classification of Verbenaceae. American Journal of Botany 97: 1647 - 1663. https: // doi. org / 10.3732 / ajb. 1000144" type="journal article" year="2010">
Marx 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE3FFC2A697FAC61A35FAF8" box="[978,1034,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE3FFC2A113FAC71B7CFAF8" author="O'Leary, N. &amp; Denham, S. S. &amp; Salimena, F. &amp; Mulgura, M. E." box="[1110,1347,1310,1336]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="197 - 219" refId="ref36872" refString="O'Leary, N., Denham, S. S., Salimena, F. &amp; Mulgura, M. E. (2012 b) Species delimitation in Lippia section Goniostachyum (Verbenaceae) using the phylogenetic species concept. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 170: 197 - 219. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8339.2012.01291. x" type="journal article" year="2012">
O’Leary 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE3FFC2A1F9FAC61ACBFAF8" box="[1212,1268,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
2012b
</bibRefCitation>
, Cardoso 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE3FFC2A5CDFA9A1F16FA9C" box="[136,297,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al. in press.</emphasis>
). The genus is characterized by the presence of branches without prickles; green or colored bracts; 2- labiate corolla and fruit splitting into 2 cluses or 2 pyrenes when mature (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE3FFC2A6F5FABF1A87FA40" author="Silva, T. R. S. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G." box="[944,1208,1382,1408]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="57 - 59" refId="ref39160" refString="Silva, T. R. S. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G. (2002) Novas combinacoes e novos sinonimos em Lippia e Lantana (Verbenaceae). Darwiniana 40: 57 - 59." type="journal article" year="2002">Silva &amp; Salimena 2002</bibRefCitation>
). There are 87 species recorded in 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFE3FFC2A44AFA531F69FA64" box="[271,342,1418,1444]" name="Brazil" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, of which 63 are endemic, with the diversity center in the 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE3FFC2A6A3FA531A7AFA64" box="[998,1093,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Cerrado</emphasis>
(64 spp.) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE3FFC2A1FAFA531EFAFA08" author="Salimena, F. R. G. &amp; Cardoso, P. H." pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refId="ref37937" refString="Salimena, F. R. G. &amp; Cardoso, P. H. (2020) Lippia in Flora do Brasil 2020 under construction. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 15170 (accessed 4 January 2021)" type="url" year="2020">Salimena &amp; Cardoso 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Forty species occur in the Atlantic Forest (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE3FFC2A7FFFA771DD4FA08" author="Salimena, F. R. G. &amp; Cardoso, P. H." box="[698,1003,1454,1480]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refId="ref37937" refString="Salimena, F. R. G. &amp; Cardoso, P. H. (2020) Lippia in Flora do Brasil 2020 under construction. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 15170 (accessed 4 January 2021)" type="url" year="2020">Salimena &amp; Cardoso 2020</bibRefCitation>
), of which four are recorded in 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFE3FFC2A016FA771EF4FA2C" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
